# ==============================================
# ChIP-seq Analysis with DESeq2
# ==============================================
# -------------------------------
# 1. Load Required Packages
# -------------------------------
library(DESeq2)          
library(ggplot2)         
library(ComplexHeatmap)  
library(pheatmap)        
# -------------------------------
# 2. Set Working Directory
# -------------------------------
setwd("C:/ChIP_seq_analysis")
# -------------------------------
# 3. Load Data
# -------------------------------
# Raw counts: rows = peaks, columns = samples
raw_counts <- readRDS("data/ChIP-seq_RawCounts.Rds")
# Sample metadata
colData <- data.frame(
  condition = factor(c(rep("Normal",6), rep("Tumor",6), rep("Encode",6))),
  row.names = colnames(raw_counts)
)
colData
# Check factor levels
levels(colData$condition)  # Encode, Normal, Tumor (Encode as default reference)
[1] "Encode" "Normal" "Tumor" 
# -------------------------------
# 4. Create DESeq2 Dataset
# -------------------------------
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(
  countData = raw_counts,
  colData = colData,
  design = ~ condition
)
# Run DESeq2
dds <- DESeq(dds)
estimating size factors
estimating dispersions
gene-wise dispersion estimates
mean-dispersion relationship
final dispersion estimates
fitting model and testing
# Check results names
resultsNames(dds)  # "Intercept" "condition_Normal_vs_Encode" "condition_Tumor_vs_Encode"
[1] "Intercept"                  "condition_Normal_vs_Encode"
[3] "condition_Tumor_vs_Encode" 
# -------------------------------
# 5. Set Reference Level
# -------------------------------
# Set Normal as reference condition
colData$condition <- relevel(colData$condition, ref = "Normal")

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(
  countData = raw_counts,
  colData = colData,
  design = ~ condition
)
dds <- DESeq(dds)
estimating size factors
estimating dispersions
gene-wise dispersion estimates
mean-dispersion relationship
final dispersion estimates
fitting model and testing
# Check results names again
resultsNames(dds)  # "Intercept" "condition_Encode_vs_Normal" "condition_Tumor_vs_Normal"
[1] "Intercept"                  "condition_Encode_vs_Normal"
[3] "condition_Tumor_vs_Normal" 
# -------------------------------
# 6. Variance-Stabilizing Transformation (VST) & PCA
# -------------------------------
vsdata <- vst(dds, blind = FALSE)

# PCA plot
plotPCA(vsdata, intgroup = "condition") +
  theme_grey() +
  labs(title = "PCA of ChIP-seq Samples")
using ntop=500 top features by variance

# -------------------------------
# 7. Differential Analysis: Tumor vs Normal
# -------------------------------
res <- results(dds, contrast = c("condition", "Tumor", "Normal"))

# Remove NA values
res <- na.omit(res)
res.df <- as.data.frame(res)
# Identify significant peaks
sigs.df <- res.df[
  res.df$padj < 0.05 & abs(res.df$log2FoldChange) > 1,
]
# -------------------------------
# 8. Volcano Plot
# -------------------------------
res.df$significant <- "No"
res.df$significant[res.df$padj < 0.05 & res.df$log2FoldChange > 1] <- "Up"
res.df$significant[res.df$padj < 0.05 & res.df$log2FoldChange < -1] <- "Down"

ggplot(res.df, aes(x = log2FoldChange, y = -log10(padj), color = significant)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.6) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("No" = "grey", "Up" = "red", "Down" = "blue")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    title = "Volcano Plot: Tumor vs Normal",
    x = "Log2 Fold Change",
    y = "-log10(FDR)"
  )

# -------------------------------
# 9. Sample Correlation Heatmap
# -------------------------------
mat <- counts(dds, normalized = TRUE)
cor_mat <- cor(mat, method = "pearson")  # Pearson correlation

pheatmap(
  cor_mat,
  color = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
  annotation_col = colData,
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_cols = TRUE,
  fontsize_row = 8,
  fontsize_col = 8,
  border_color = NA
)

# -------------------------------
# 10. Heatmap of Significant Peaks
# -------------------------------
mat_sig <- counts(dds, normalized = TRUE)[rownames(sigs.df), ]

# Scale rows (z-score)
mat_sig.z <- t(apply(mat_sig, 1, scale))
colnames(mat_sig.z) <- colnames(mat_sig)

pheatmap(
  mat_sig.z,
  color = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_cols = TRUE,
  show_rownames = FALSE,
  annotation_col = colData
)

# -------------------------------
# 11. Top Peaks Heatmap
# -------------------------------
# Select top 30 peaks by absolute log2 fold change
top_peaks <- rownames(sigs.df[order(abs(sigs.df$log2FoldChange), decreasing = TRUE), ])[1:30]
mat_top <- counts(dds, normalized = TRUE)[top_peaks, ]

# Scale rows
mat_top.z <- t(apply(mat_top, 1, scale))
colnames(mat_top.z) <- colnames(mat_top)

pheatmap(
  mat_top.z,
  color = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  cluster_cols = TRUE,
  show_rownames = TRUE,
  annotation_col = colData,
  border_color = NA,
  fontsize_row = 6,
  fontsize_col = 6
)
